Steps to Integrate GCP Pub/Sub with Power Automate
Create a Pub/Sub Topic in GCP
Navigate to the Pub/Sub page in the Google Cloud Console.
Click Create Topic, enter a Topic ID, and click Create.
Create a Power Automate Flow (Receiver)
Create a new Instant Cloud Flow and select the When an HTTP request is received trigger.
Note: This trigger generates a URL only after the flow is saved.
Create a Push Subscription in GCP
Go to your created Topic and click Create Subscription.
Under Delivery Type, select Push.
In the Endpoint URL field, paste the URL generated by the Power Automate "HTTP request" trigger.
Save the subscription.
Test the Flow
Go to the Pub/Sub Topic in GCP and use the "Publish Message" feature to send a test payload.
The Power Automate flow will trigger, receiving the message in JSON format. 
Key Considerations
Authentication: Ensure the Pub/Sub push subscription is configured to handle HTTPS appropriately (often via public URL or by setting up authentication if using API Management in front of Flow).
Acknowledgment: When Power Automate returns an HTTP 200/202 status, Pub/Sub considers the message delivered and removes it from the queue.
Alternatives: If you cannot use a Push Subscription, you can use a scheduled Power Automate flow with the Google Cloud connector (if available) or an HTTP connector to "Pull" messages, though this is less real-time. 
